gomodel:SYNGO_4856  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7: Tamalin knockdown did not have any effect on the surface expression of GluA1-containing receptors. Chemically induced mGluR-mediated AMPAR endocytosis was disrupted after shRNA knockdown of Tamalin, rescued by WT Tamalin but not by mutated Tamalin where its S-SCAM (gene MAGI2) interaction site was disabled.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Dissociated primary hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from C57BL/6 P0 mouse pups of both sexes as described previously with minor changes\"\n\nantibody:\nanti-tamalin antibody from Rockland Immunochemicals (USA)\nFull-length mouse tamalin was obtained from Shigetada Nakanishi (Osaka Bioscience Institute, Japan)\n\n\"We first identified a highly effective shRNA to tamalin (shTam) that robustly reduced the endogenous tamalin levels in dissociated neuron cultures when assessed by immunocytochemistry and Western blotting. The shRNA against tamalin (shTam) was cloned in a multipromoter vector under the control of the H1 promoter targeting the tamalin sequence GCATCTATGACACACTGGAGT\"\n\nNucleotide BLAST confirms this is GenBank accession NM_019518 (which matches the annotated uniprot accession)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2022-09-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4856" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

